An example

From an ImageId we get the pixel coordinates or the mask for every defect. Here an example of steel image.

{% raw %} 
img_id = "72aaba8ad.jpg"
tmp_df = train[train['ImageId'] == img_id]
img_path = train_path / img_id
im = Image.open(img_path)

print(tmp_df[["ImageId", "ClassId"]]); im

            ImageId  ClassId
3136  72aaba8ad.jpg        4
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
height, width = im.shape
height, width

(256, 1600)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
assert height == 256
assert width == 1600
{% endraw %}

Discovery defect functions

{% raw %}

defeat_position[source]

defeat_position()

Get coordinates of defects (x, y) given an ImageId and a ClassId

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
x,y = defeat_position(img_id=img_id, class_id=4)
x.shape, y.shape

((24515,), (24515,))
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

rle_to_mask[source]

rle_to_mask(rle:str, class_id:int, height:int, width:int)

Convert RLE encoded pixels to numpy array for only one class_id

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
im = rle_to_mask(tmp_df["EncodedPixels"].item(), tmp_df["ClassId"].item(), height, width)

plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))
plt.imshow(im)
plt.show()
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

multi_rle_to_mask[source]

multi_rle_to_mask()

Convert all RLE encoded pixels for an image and returns the mask

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
im = multi_rle_to_mask(img_path)

plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))
plt.imshow(im)
plt.show()
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

Show multiple images

{% raw %}

show_defects[source]

show_defects(class_id=None, n=20, only_defects=True, multi_defects=False)

Plot multiple images

class_id: str or int If provided, all plots have this class_id

n: int Num of images to plot

only_defects : bool, default True If False it shows even the no faulty images

multi_defects : bool, default False If True it shows imgs with multi defects

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
show_defects(class_id=1, n=1)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
show_defects(class_id=2, n=1)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
show_defects(class_id=3, n=1)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
show_defects(class_id=4, n=1)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
show_defects(n=1, multi_defects=True)
